commit_message:
Improve Neutron subnets management

Previously, subnet had some parameters as read-only which blocks some
features, like specifing dns servers, allocation pools and also specific
host routes.
This patch aims to add support for these options as well for creation
and also for update (for some of them where API allows it).

Change-Id: Ibf71fa8577ca8799cdd5767726e9c0ea4a23a5fc
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>

commit_message:
Take a vm out of SNAPSHOTTING after Glance error

If a snapshot is attempted to be taken when Glance can't find the
underlying image (usually because it's been deleted), then ImageNotFound
is raised to nova.compute.manager.ComputeManager._snapshot_instance. The
error path for this leaves the instance in a snapshotting state; after
which "operator intervention" is required.

This simply reverts the instance state under that specific circumstance.

DocImpact: previously a snapshot that failed for this reason would leave
the instance in a spurious snapshotting task state indefinitely. Now,
the task state is reverted. At the moment that revert is 'silent'
(although the failure to snapshot will be evident to the user).

Fixes-bug: #1267097
(cherry picked from commit 96dba50737819c24b4ddd9cb1078da305638abc9)

Conflicts:

	nova/compute/manager.py

Change-Id: I9623cfaed31e8337ab65bc1eab85ad3b51b1a5ca

subject: Explicity teardown on error in libguestfs setup()
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-03-04 15:41:27.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/disk/vfs/guestfs.py'], 'message': 'Explicity teardown on error in libguestfs setup()

Previously, in the setup method of the libguestfs driver
for Nova's VFS, on an error the handle object was simply
dereferenced (set to None), and then an new error was thrown.
This relied on an implicit close() on the handle being called
by GC.  However, in some cases the setup progresses far enough
that the implicit close is not enough, and leaves an "orphaned"
libguestfs VM.

Now, the teardown() method is called explicitly, which ensures that
no "orphaned" VMs are left around in case of an error.

Change-Id: I7fbe470046ce6c76bc13d77d8df360351a3ef715
Fixes: bug #1270304
(cherry picked from commit fa62cfe15fd6dddecf657966d166a2d3a2bdd317)
'}]
commit_message:
Explicity teardown on error in libguestfs setup()

Previously, in the setup method of the libguestfs driver
for Nova's VFS, on an error the handle object was simply
dereferenced (set to None), and then an new error was thrown.
This relied on an implicit close() on the handle being called
by GC.  However, in some cases the setup progresses far enough
that the implicit close is not enough, and leaves an "orphaned"
libguestfs VM.

Now, the teardown() method is called explicitly, which ensures that
no "orphaned" VMs are left around in case of an error.

Change-Id: I7fbe470046ce6c76bc13d77d8df360351a3ef715
Fixes: bug #1270304

revisions:
[{'number': 8, 'created': '2014-03-11 12:57:53.000000000', 'files': ['trove/tests/unittests/guestagent/test_volume.py', 'trove/guestagent/volume.py'], 'message': 'Fixes insecure update of /etc/fstab file

Reasons:
- While updating /etc/fstab in write_to_fstab in
  trove/guestagent/volume.py, the temporary file-name was easy to
  guess and had a permanent name making it prone to unwanted access.
- The temporary file-permission was set to 666, making it insecure.

Changes:
- Uses NamedTemporaryFile for temporary file creation.
- Used file reading instead of copying the file.
- These changes eliminate the chances of guessing the file-name,
  as well as updating the same.

Change-Id: I07c3980e40fe218d35605a851a17535cd3972c11
Closes-Bug: #1267991
'}]
commit_message:
Fixes insecure update of /etc/fstab file

Reasons:
- While updating /etc/fstab in write_to_fstab in
  trove/guestagent/volume.py, the temporary file-name was easy to
  guess and had a permanent name making it prone to unwanted access.
- The temporary file-permission was set to 666, making it insecure.

Changes:
- Uses NamedTemporaryFile for temporary file creation.
- Used file reading instead of copying the file.
- These changes eliminate the chances of guessing the file-name,
  as well as updating the same.

Change-Id: I07c3980e40fe218d35605a851a17535cd3972c11
Closes-Bug: #1267991

commit_message:
Refactoring code that gives possibility define admin tenant name for Neutron.

In this commit removed unnecessary parameters.
Tenant's name gets from Neutron config if given there, from fuel_config hash
if not given in Neutron config and set to "admin" if not given anywhere.

Closes-bug: #1284189

[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-03-11 00:25:19.000000000', 'files': ['elements/testenv-worker/testenv-worker'], 'message': 'Allow the testenv client to dictate the worker timeout

The testenv client is privileged to information about jobs that the
worker is not aware of, so allow the client to send us the appropriate
timeout.

This also changes the format of the the data sent to us from the client
to a json representation of a python dict.

Change-Id: If3f082c04d937f0d5baa09cf002aef797eebcbe5
'}]
commit_message:
Allow the testenv client to dictate the worker timeout

The testenv client is privileged to information about jobs that the
worker is not aware of, so allow the client to send us the appropriate
timeout.

This also changes the format of the the data sent to us from the client
to a json representation of a python dict.

Change-Id: If3f082c04d937f0d5baa09cf002aef797eebcbe5

subject: Set default values for repo location and ref
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-03-19 06:29:45.000000000', 'files': ['scripts/pull-tools'], 'message': "Set default values for repo location and ref

Steal code from diskimage-builder's source-repositories element to make
sure that we never reference an unbound variable.

First we populate the name of a potential variable into an _OVERRIDE
variable; then we set the real variable to either the contents of a
variable with that name or the default.

This avoids any chance of ever referencing an unbound variable, even in
an eval.

Also, change the message displayed in the case that the tool is already
checked out, but not on the master branch, and DIB_REPOREF_tool is not
set, to be clearer about why we're skipping the pull of that repo

Change-Id: Ib98b20dbacfc8cdf948bee1265adc9485894c73f
Closes-Bug: #1294477
"}]
commit_message:
Set default values for repo location and ref

Steal code from diskimage-builder's source-repositories element to make
sure that we never reference an unbound variable.

First we populate the name of a potential variable into an _OVERRIDE
variable; then we set the real variable to either the contents of a
variable with that name or the default.

This avoids any chance of ever referencing an unbound variable, even in
an eval.

Also, change the message displayed in the case that the tool is already
checked out, but not on the master branch, and DIB_REPOREF_tool is not
set, to be clearer about why we're skipping the pull of that repo

Change-Id: Ib98b20dbacfc8cdf948bee1265adc9485894c73f
Closes-Bug: #1294477

subject: Workaround: easy_install can't install six from wheels.
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2014-03-18 09:35:53.000000000', 'files': ['elements/openstack-clients/bin/install-openstack-client', 'elements/os-svc-install/bin/os-svc-install'], 'message': "Workaround: easy_install can't install six from wheels.

Using a wheel-based pypi-mirror, some dependencies will fail
to install during venv creation. This comes down to the fact
that the entire universe of Python package installation tools
don't (yet) grok wheels - so things that lean on easy_install,
for example, can fail.

This patch is a workaround - longer term, this needs to be
chased with the upstream software.

Closes-bug: #1288942

Change-Id: Ic6fe1393bb7a6e6550314d074b2079ea9fc6aa45
"}]
commit_message:
Workaround: easy_install can't install six from wheels.

Using a wheel-based pypi-mirror, some dependencies will fail
to install during venv creation. This comes down to the fact
that the entire universe of Python package installation tools
don't (yet) grok wheels - so things that lean on easy_install,
for example, can fail.

This patch is a workaround - longer term, this needs to be
chased with the upstream software.

Closes-bug: #1288942

Change-Id: Ic6fe1393bb7a6e6550314d074b2079ea9fc6aa45

commit_message:
Fix incorrect QPID rpc_backend property

With notifier_strategy set to qpid the Glance-API fails to start due to
its rpc_backend driver being incorrect, it's the nova one, instead of
the glance one.

Change-Id: Ic697a827988ccddbe7c5ff3258d231d22d08d838
Closes-Bug: #1294333

commit_message:
multi-backend: configure default type

This patch aims to
- configure a default type in cinder-volume (without it, a volume can't
  boot without explicitly specifying a type from the client, which could
lead to errors)
- add unit tests for cinder::backends class

Change-Id: Ia0a475a629576596dd60e513bf0764e9bc3000ab
Signed-off-by: Emilien Macchi <emilien.macchi@enovance.com>
(cherry picked from commit 690e16d290fe80320820f29cc82463b3bbdca48c)

commit_message:
Add listing tested APIs for v3

In the Icehouse design summit QA session, we've discussed "coverage
analysis tooling" and decided to refresh and use this patch[1].
This patch is for catching called Nova APIs and creating a report on
integration tests. When start catching, every called API will be
caught.
To enable this function, 'api_coverage=True' is needed in nova.conf.
This patch is for v3 APIs.

[1] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/icehouse-summit-qa-coverage-tooling

blueprint: list-tested-apis
DocImpact

Change-Id: Ib90886fc95a07b817efadd773fd62fb7cfc9c35a

commit_message:
Added Backup/Restore validations

Added checks for backup-create API call to ensure
datastore supports backup strategy
Also for trove-create API call (when restoring from backup)
added checks to ensure that datastore version of backup
being restored matches with datastore version of
instance being created

Closes-Bug: #1285876

commit_message:
Uses explicit imports for _

Previously `_` was monkeypatched in tests/core.py and bin/keystone-*.
This meant that if a developer was not running the tests exactly as
the documentation described they would not work. Even importing
certain modules in a interactive Python interpreter would fail unless
keystone.tests was imported first. Monkeypatching was removed and
explicit import for `_` was added.

Co-Authored-By: David Stanek <dstanek@dstanek.com>
Change-Id: I8b25b5b6d83fb873e25a8fab7686babf1d2261fa
Closes-Bug: #1255518

commit_message:
VMware: Clone snapshots to the Glance datastore

Glance contains a new backend store since Icehouse: the VMware store.
The Nova VMware driver should take advantage of it for snapshots:
instead of uploading the bits through the network, we move them
to the Glance datastore folder and register a new location for the
image. This makes the snapshot operation much faster.

This optimization is built on top of the image handler framework
using the push_image() api.

partially implements bp vmware-clone-image-handler

Change-Id: I7fdbed84749cfa9d9a440ba591a24bbac522d7ff

commit_message:
Deploy VM to SDRS datastore cluster (Phase 1)

This code change intends to enable the capability of vmware driver
to deploy VM to SDRS enabled datastore cluster.

In order to implement that, two options need to be added to
nova.conf. The first option is 'datastore_cluster_name'. This option
allows the end user to specify the name of datastore cluster
(StoragePod object). The second option is 'use_SDRS'. This is a
boolean option. The end user can use it to specify whether or not to
utilize SDRS to select datastore. This option will have effect, only
if datastore_cluster_name is specified.

The VM image need to be a template in VCenter, so that SDRS will
automatically execute VM provisioning task.

If the image is a template in VCenter, and use_SDRS is false, vmware
driver need to select a datastore and call cloneVM_Task() to deploy
the VM. In this case, if datastore_cluster_name is speicified, it
will have effect to filter the datastores from user defined datastore
cluster.

If the image is a template in VCenter, and use_SDRS is true and
datastore_cluster_name is also speicified, vmware driver will call
RecommendDatastores() to deploy the VM. If SDRS is not fully automated,
ApplyStorageDrsRecommendation_Task() need to be called.

All these code changes will be proposed in two phases. In phase 1, only
selecting datastore from datastore cluster will be implemented. The code
to invoke RecommendDatastores() will be implemented in phase 2.

DocImpact

Change-Id: Ic0cf74ea65ea90c15688d1ce0f874cf8b953e630
Partially implements: blueprint vmware-sdrs-datastore-cluster

commit_message:
Proxy neutron configuration to guest instance.

Exposes network data from neutron in both config drive and
metadata service. Information is available only if neutron is
enabled. The data available is fairly similar to the neutron
get port details API with some more information about the fixed
ips and in particular more information about the subnet.

The network data is available as
GET: http://169.254.169.254/openstack/latest/network_data

DocImpact

Change-Id: If06142ab0b606533183a25232916ecd421e38259
Implements: blueprint metadata-service-network-info

commit_message:
Pass Instance obj to get_console_output

The get_console_output method in the compute manager already used the Instance
object internally.  This patch updates the API side to pass the instance in
Instance object form over rpc instead of manually converting it on the manager
side.

Part of blueprint compute-manager-objects

Change-Id: Ifda9f6efc1f59595d6040c4617acc299347d17af

Downgrades or remove some LOG.exception messages in the V2 API
to a more appropriate level in cases where we a traceback

commit_message:
Duplicate security group name cause fail to start instance

When create a security group, the duplicate name is allowed.
In create a instance, duplicate sg name will cause exception and
the instance will be started fail. So the duplicate name of sg
should be not allowed.

Change-Id: I28015b28d5a46869d0ac3ea34355da888c279828
Closes-Bug: #1289195

commit_message:
Retrieve missing container command after pulling from index

Docker driver spawns container with wrong command "sh"
if image doesn't exists on nova node.
'Cmd' assigned before pulling image, hence docker 'inspect'
of unexisting image returns empty command.
Solution: refactor code to first check if image exists,
pull if not and inspect only after pulling.

Change-Id: Id30d20bb57946ab11f67c96ffbb5907006b6d558
Closes-Bug: #1266875

commit_message:
Reduced database overhead from agents

 - added dedicated handler for node agents update only requests
 - caching data from agents to avoid db update with same data
 - nailgun responses with appropriate http statuses
 - changed agent update logic. Now it tries to update first and respects
   nailgun response statuses

Change-Id: I2658cf7561cd8c9116acced2443d072d471f3bdb
Implements: blueprint nailgun-agent-handler
Closes-Bug: #1274614

commit_message:
Cells: Pass instance objects to update/delete_instance_metadata

When nova-cells processes a 'run_compute_api_method' message it pulls
the instance from the local db and calls the appropriate compute api
method with a sqlalchemy model.  Since the update_instance_metadata and
delete_instance_metadata methods in the compute api require objects
these methods are added to the list of methods that will receive an
object.

Change-Id: Iaa5ba6878f0162e2fab8dd3e4b87ea8dd3d527f6
Closes-bug: #1290975

commit_message:
Kill 'Skipping unknown group key: firewall_driver' log trace

This is done by trying to import the option first. If this
does not work, emit a warning instead as in most cases this is
harmless for a number of reasons: a) the service might not
even need the opt; b) if things do break down the line, we'll
see bigger traces; c) it's not gonna be long for this legacy
quantum/neutron stuff to be removed altogether.

Closes-bug: 1210121

Change-Id: I34917da9cb6117ee1d42140621c742f503279b6b

commit_message:
Verify service attributes through Nova os-quota-sets API

This patch adds checks whether a response of Nova os-flavor-access API
includes the attributes to block the backward incompatibility change
in the future.

The response body of v2 API is the following:
{
    "quota_set": {
        "id": "231a1e7fd1b344f9874d0334d98b459c",
        "instances": 10,
        "cores": 20,
        "ram": 51200,
        "floating_ips": 10,
        "fixed_ips": -1,
        "metadata_items": 128,
        "injected_files": 5,
        "injected_file_content_bytes": 10240,
        "injected_file_path_bytes": 255,
        "key_pairs": 100,
        "security_groups": 10
        "security_group_rules": 20,
    }
}

The one of v3 API is the following:
{
    "quota_set": {
        "id": "231a1e7fd1b344f9874d0334d98b459c",
        "instances": 10,
        "cores": 20,
        "ram": 51200,
        "floating_ips": 10,
        "fixed_ips": -1,
        "metadata_items": 128,
        "key_pairs": 100,
        "security_groups": 10
        "security_group_rules": 20,
    }
}

Partially implements blueprint nova-api-attribute-test

Change-Id: I70f61fbf8fa71d04cea5196cfba1ef0aecfecb9d

commit_message:
Fix EC2 credentials create to use admin user credentials.

Keystone has changed to no longer authenticate with the bootstrap
token for EC2 creds.The identity LWRP has been change to bootstrap
the admin user and then use admin creds (not the bootstrap token)
to create EC2 creds.

Closes-Bug: #1274870

Change-Id: I96b9f18b84194e2128a867cb6b89ba8b24c59d6e

revisions:

The bootstrap process hard-codes the repos it checks out for
tripleo-incubator, tripleo-image-elements, diskimage-builder,
and tripleo-heat-templates.

This adds support for DIB_REPOLOCATION / DIB_REPOREF variables
to the bootstrap process.

Although the environment variables might be technically misnamed
(since they're used by the bootstrap process, before DIB gets a
look-in), I picked those so that they'll work with any environment-
setting script that trawls a directory of checkouts to set these up

"}]
commit_message:
Use the DIB_REPOLOCATION / DIB_REPOREF for the bootstrap.

The bootstrap process hard-codes the repos it checks out for
tripleo-incubator, tripleo-image-elements, diskimage-builder,
and tripleo-heat-templates.

This adds support for DIB_REPOLOCATION / DIB_REPOREF variables
to the bootstrap process.

Although the environment variables might be technically misnamed
(since they're used by the bootstrap process, before DIB gets a
look-in), I picked those so that they'll work with any environment-
setting script that trawls a directory of checkouts to set these up
prior to invoking devtest.sh.

This is just a small convenience whilst working on the incubator
itself.

Change-Id: I33e16cb3946519a686c1692f5e2d39424c13bcbf

commit_message:
Add metering configuration for nova

There are various attributes that need to be configured for nova to
start posting notifications for ceilometer to keep track of things.

This patch adds those attributes, and it additionally adds a single
property that can be set to automatically set them all on with sensible
defaults as described here:
http://docs.openstack.org/developer/ceilometer/install/manual.html

commit_message:
Fix difference between mysql & psql of flavor-show

If you create a new flavor using a deleted flavorid,
the result of flavor-show is different between mysql and psql.

This issue is caused by the different processing for index in each db.

We need to specify the sort-type to avoid the issue.

Change-Id: Ib1029e80c1b981e1ec86d954b63f83650c9b1cc1
Closes-Bug: #1288636

commit_message:
Libvirt: Repair metadata injection into guests

The change to use Instance objects when spawning instances
changed the format of the 'metadata' property.  But this wasn't
taken into account in the code which actually injects metadata
into /meta.js in the guest's fs.

This patch ensures that the meta.js file injection expects the
new format.

Closes-bug: #1284733

Change-Id: I37049ac01b65d30d588578e351fcddac457f95a7

[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-01-20 14:26:21.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/virt/vmwareapi/test_driver_api.py'], 'message': "VMware: Ensure test VM is running in rescue tests

Code was calling get_info() on test VM, but not using it. There are 2
options to fix this:

1. Use it
2. Don't call get_info()

I have chosen option 1.

This change adds a test on the data returned by get_info() which
ensures that the vm just created is in state power_state.RUNNING. The
code later tests that the vm is in state power_state.SHUTDOWN, so the
additional test that it was previously running reinforces that
rescue() caused the shutdown to happen.

Change-Id: Iec58b0dd40702d3bcebf339e9ada8b90a2229d5c
"}]
commit_message:
VMware: Ensure test VM is running in rescue tests

Code was calling get_info() on test VM, but not using it. There are 2
options to fix this:

1. Use it
2. Don't call get_info()

I have chosen option 1.

This change adds a test on the data returned by get_info() which
ensures that the vm just created is in state power_state.RUNNING. The
code later tests that the vm is in state power_state.SHUTDOWN, so the
additional test that it was previously running reinforces that
rescue() caused the shutdown to happen.

Change-Id: Iec58b0dd40702d3bcebf339e9ada8b90a2229d5c

[{'number': 16, 'created': '2014-03-17 02:23:41.000000000', 'files': ['nova/tests/compute/test_compute_api.py', 'nova/compute/api.py'], 'message': "Fix auto confirmation failed because of db access

The _reserve_quota_delta() method in compute/api.py reserves
quotas in DB if deltas is not empty, and it will be called by
confirm_resize method.
If the confirm resize operation is launched from users through
RESTful API, this direct DB access is allowed, and the confirm
operation will succeed.
But if the confirm operation is launched from nova-compute
through periodic task '_poll_unconfirmed_resizes', this direct
DB access is forbidden and the auto confirmation is failed.

This change fixes the above bug by using quota object while
reserving quota deltas.

Closes-bug: #1262461

Change-Id: I852452e9a62b167e6e620e85f12ab5f19974e2d8
"}]
commit_message:
Fix auto confirmation failed because of db access

The _reserve_quota_delta() method in compute/api.py reserves
quotas in DB if deltas is not empty, and it will be called by
confirm_resize method.
If the confirm resize operation is launched from users through
RESTful API, this direct DB access is allowed, and the confirm
operation will succeed.
But if the confirm operation is launched from nova-compute
through periodic task '_poll_unconfirmed_resizes', this direct
DB access is forbidden and the auto confirmation is failed.

This change fixes the above bug by using quota object while
reserving quota deltas.

Closes-bug: #1262461

Change-Id: I852452e9a62b167e6e620e85f12ab5f19974e2d8

commit_message:
VMware: fix the VNC port allocation

There is small chance for VNC port collisions with the current
implementation which choose the port number based on the MoRef id
of the VM.
This patch fixes this by running a query for all allocated ports
and then selects one which is not taken.

Closes-Bug: #1255609
(cherry picked from commit 2f49ed4b5dbb5c954fc7a9b42ee7b170c38c775c)

Conflicts:

	nova/exception.py
	nova/tests/virt/vmwareapi/test_vmwareapi.py
	nova/tests/virt/vmwareapi/test_vmwareapi_vm_util.py
	nova/virt/vmwareapi/vm_util.py
	nova/virt/vmwareapi/vmops.py

commit_message:
Add unit tests for wait_for_resource_deletion

This commit adds unit tests to cover the wait_for_resource_deletion
method in the rest client. It covers the 3 cases for the method:
the resource is deleted before the timeout, the timeout is hit and an
exception is raised, and the service client child class doesn't have
a is_resource_deleted() method.

Partially implements bp unit-tests

Change-Id: I2acd1b5f44a7526c4b38d17d37bdc4b0f5db7d54

commit_message:
resolve KeyError for IBM Storwize/SVC driver

When using iSCSI protocol to conenct IBM v7000, and compression
is not enabled for the system, KeyError may occur because of the response
item's lack of 'license_compression_enclosures'. So add a check to
resolve it.

Change-Id: Ie53631ea5b047650897313ad5614f6e1df5377f2
Closes-Bug: #1288645

commit_message:
Fix ensure log_config is absent regression

This fixes a regression what was introduced
with the minor refactoring patch
(79c5bbba98458d2e7db80d0797b6b7991703cb7a).

W/o this patch nova, cinder and ceilometer would not be
re-configured, if debug=true was re-set in astute.yaml
CI retest

commit_message:

There is a race condition waiting for "!= 0" because it is entirely
possible nova refreshed the compute hosts list in between baremetal node
registrations, leading to a number != 0, but also not high enough to
create the overcloud.

commit_message:
Made mkfs arguments optional and added rootdelay

The problem is that we have been creating file
systems with -f flag while it is suitable only for
xfs, but not for any other file systems. Another
problem is that some hardware such as ancient Dell
equipment delays exposing raid volumes and grub
usually fails not waiting for root file system is
available. rootdelay=90 allows to avoid that kind of
unexpected behaviour.

Change-Id: I199077b4bf53fdcdc17a89fb4c8ad82bfd966a87

subject: Replacing NetworkGateway when devices updated
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-03-13 10:54:14.000000000', 'files': ['heat/engine/resources/neutron/network_gateway.py', 'heat/tests/test_neutron_network_gateway.py'], 'message': "Replacing NetworkGateway when devices updated

Updating OS::Neutron::NetworkGateway failed when devices property changed.

Currently, NetworkGateway's devices property doesn't have update_allowed=True.
So, UpdateReplace have used when updating devices property.
However, Neutron doesn't allow that same Gateway Services ID exist at a time.
Eventually, 409 error occured by Neutron.

For avoiding above error, I implemented replacing NetworkGateway in handle_update.
The processing order is delete -> create. It can avoid the 409 error.

Change-Id: I4021610355d03eb6ca07272cb1e44ff2b31dfff9
Closes-bug: #1291901
"}]
commit_message:
Replacing NetworkGateway when devices updated

Updating OS::Neutron::NetworkGateway failed when devices property changed.

Currently, NetworkGateway's devices property doesn't have update_allowed=True.
So, UpdateReplace have used when updating devices property.
However, Neutron doesn't allow that same Gateway Services ID exist at a time.
Eventually, 409 error occured by Neutron.

For avoiding above error, I implemented replacing NetworkGateway in handle_update.
The processing order is delete -> create. It can avoid the 409 error.

Change-Id: I4021610355d03eb6ca07272cb1e44ff2b31dfff9
Closes-bug: #1291901

commit_message:
Raise exception if volume snapshot id not found instead of return

In V2 API, if show or delete a snapshot with an unknown id, exception
will be returned instead of raised. Even though correct error
will be returned to client, it's not aligned to other API layer
code, this patch modify it by raise exception instead of return.

Change-Id: I22d4565ca08e1c0ed5041ce903bf6ba918c14cfd
Closes-Bug: #1279189

commit_message:
Fix compatibility link creation for mysql.sock on openSUSE

Create the /var/run/mysql/mysql.sock compatibility link already during the
pre-configure run. Otherwise e.g. the "reset-db" script called during the
"boot-stack" element's configure run will fail to find the mysql socket.

Change-Id: I8046f8d056e7d28e046ccfdfd22f6b73338352b6

commit_message:
Raise NotImplementedError in NeutronV2 API

Remove unused code in nova.network.neutronv2 that returns an empty
list. Instead of just returning an empty list, let's be more explicit
and raise a NotImplementedError. This will be more descriptive if
someone is trying to use this part of the NeutronAPI.

Commit 45e92d4703 contains the changes to use the db layer instead of
the network rpcapi.

Change-Id: I2a9ada8186fd4165c7fceb15965055b5793e6e2c
Closes-Bug: 1258380

commit_message:
Add version 2.0 of conductor rpc interface

This commit adds a new major revision to the rpc interface used to
talk to the conductor service.  The old version will be retained in
Icehouse for Havana rolling upgrade capability.  1.x can be dropped
as soon as Juno development opens.

When 1.x gets dropped, we will be able to remove the following methods
from the conductor manager, as well as all other supporting code for
these methods throughout the conductor:

 - ping()
 - instance_get()
 - instance_get_all()
 - migration_get()
 - migration_get_unconfirmed_by_dest_compute()
 - migration_create()
 - migration_update()
 - aggregate_get()
 - aggregate_get_by_host()
 - aggregate_metadata_add()
 - aggregate_metadata_delete()
 - get_backdoor_port()
 - security_group_get_by_instance()
 - security_group_rule_get_by_security_group()
 - block_device_mapping_destroy()
 - instance_get_all_hung_in_rebooting()
 - instance_info_cache_update()
 - instance_type_get()
 - vol_get_usage_by_time()
 - vol_usage_update()
 - compute_stop()
 - compute_confirm_resize()
 - compute_reboot()

We can also drop backwards compatibility handling for the absence of
any parameters added to other methods during 1.x.

Note that the client side will only send 2.0 messages, but that's
fine.  We expect the nova-conductor service to get updated at the same
time as, or before anything that uses this client code.

For more information on this type of change, see:
https://wiki.openstack.org/wiki/RpcMajorVersionUpdates

Part of blueprint rpc-major-version-updates-icehouse

Change-Id: Ic443c02b1342cceb8c86c37b51af03094157bc48

commit_message:
Cells API calls return 501 when cells disabled

When cells is not enabled the cells API calls should return
a 501 NotImplemented rather than have the internals
eventually raise various errors which may include timeout
errors.

+DocImpact: cells API calls will now return a 501 if cells is disabled
Closes-Bug: 1288214

Change-Id: I07e69bbe11ec88cd3f07b47846f3a0a5c9e6f3dc
